<subSubSection pageId="62" pageNumber="63" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="62.[151,1437,151,861]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,367,392]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Kiener, 1834" authorityName="Kiener" authorityYear="1834" box="[322,763,367,392]" class="Gastropoda" family="Nassariidae" genus="Nassarius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="62" pageNumber="63" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="scalariformis">
<emphasis box="[322,590,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">Nassarius scalariformis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Kiener" box="[606,754,367,392]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63" refString="Kiener, L. C. (1834) Species general et iconographie des coquilles vivantes. 9. Famille des Purpuriferes. Deuxieme partie. Genre Buccin. Rousseau et J. - B. Bailliere, Paris, 112 pp." type="book" year="1834">Kiener, 1834</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Philippi, 1836" authorityName="Philippi" authorityYear="1836" box="[818,1206,367,392]" class="Gastropoda" family="Nassariidae" genus="Nassarius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="62" pageNumber="63" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="limatus">
<emphasis box="[818,1021,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">Nassarius limatus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Philippi" box="[1035,1197,367,392]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63" refString="Philippi, R. A. (1836) Enumeratio molluscorum Siciliae cum viventium tum in tellure tertiaria fossilium, quae in itinere suo observavit. Schropp, Berlin, XIV + 267 pp." type="book" year="1836">Philippi, 1836</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
(the latter also cited as being introduced by Deshayes in 1844) are currently regarded as junior synonyms of the present taxon (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Cernohorsky" box="[151,363,439,464]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63" refString="Cernohorsky, W. O. (1984) Systematics of the family Nassariidae (Mollusca: Gastropoda). Bulletin of the Auckland Institute and Museum, 14, 1 - 356." type="journal article" year="1984">Cernohorsky 1984</bibRefCitation>
). It is not clear whether 
<taxonomicName authority="Brocchi, 1814" authorityName="Brocchi" authorityYear="1814" box="[635,988,439,464]" class="Gastropoda" family="Nassariidae" genus="Nassarius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="62" pageNumber="63" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="prysmaticus">
<emphasis box="[635,803,441,464]" italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">N. prysmaticus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Brocchi" box="[818,980,439,464]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63" refString="Brocchi, G. B. (1814) Conchiologia fossile subapennina con osservazioni geologiche sugli Apennini e sul suolo adiacente. Stamperia Reale, Milano, LXXX + 56 + 712 pp. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 11569" type="book" year="1814">Brocchi, 1814</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
could represent a senior synonym of 
<taxonomicName class="Gastropoda" family="Nassariidae" genus="Nassarius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="62" pageNumber="63" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="lima">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">N. lima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, since the only reliable difference seems to be the shape of the protoconch (cf. 
<bibRefCitation author="Adam" box="[1087,1337,476,501]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63" refString="Adam, W. &amp; Glibert, M. (1976) Observations sur le &quot; groupe &quot; de Nassarius clathratus (Born, 1778) (Mollusca, Prosobranchia). Bulletin de l'Institut Royal des Sciences Naturelles de Belgique, 51 (4), 1 - 69." type="journal article" year="1976">Adam &amp; Glibert 1976</bibRefCitation>
, p. 53).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="62.[151,1437,151,861]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,339,511,536]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">Occurrence</emphasis>
. Box-corer samples BC67 (13 specimens), BC70 (6), BC71 (6), BC72 (129); cores BC04 (1), BC05 (1), BC21 (4), BC51 (5), BC67 (3), BC72 (9). Maximum height: 
